   RAC-NASCAR-FRANCE _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ NASCAR president Bill
France today turned over control of the racing circuit's daily
operations to Mike Helton. The move marks the first time France or
his late father, Bill France Sr., hasn't been in charge of NASCAR
since the circuit was formed 51 years ago. France will remain
NASCAR's president, while Helton will be senior vice president and
chief operating officer. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
