<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACH _ WASHINGTON _ Senators hope to wrap up today (Thursday)
the only impeachment trial of this century. Yesterday Senate
Majority Leader Trent Lott said that ``if at all possible'' he
would like to set a vote for 5 p.m. EST Thursday on whether to
convict Clinton on the perjury and obstruction of justice charges _
votes that by all signs will fall far short of the two-thirds
majority needed to oust the nation's 42nd president. Sen . Paul
Coverdell asked if Senators could submit their statements without
reading them, which could speed up the deliberation process.
(Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/IMPEACH-SCORECARD _ WASHINGTON _ A number of Senators
announced today how they will be voting and described what they
told their colleagues during the deliberations. (Foskett, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WASTE _ WASHINGTON _ At least 26 government programs have wasted
a total of $30 billion through fraud and mismanagement, a House
committee reported Wednesday. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   ATT-COMPETITION _ WASHINGTON _ AT&AMP;T and the regional Bell
telephone companies, locked in fierce competition for expanding
phone services, hold dueling press appearances Wednesday. (Regan,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
