   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Feb. 11. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
CLINTON-TAPES (Washington) - A disclosure that a U.S. intelligence
agency may have taped White House telephone conversations was not
intended by Republican senators to influence the impeachment trial
of the president, Sen. Jon Kyl said Wednesday. ``It has zero impact
on the impeachment. It simply is sent it down to OIC (Kenneth
Starr's office), and the impeachment trial goes down. We're going
to have a vote on Friday. It's not going to slow it down. If we had
wanted to do that, we would have sought to bring everything to a
screeching halt until we verified the information one way or
another. It was kept very quiet until it got out and there was no
effort by our leadership to insert it into the impeachment
process.'' Meanwhile, White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said he
was not aware of any recordings or transcripts that resulted from
an outside agency monitoring the president's calls. By JEFF BARKER.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
AZNOTES (Phoenix) - Arizonans comment on the Clinton impeachment
trial. By JULIE AMPARANO. Story will movein the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
AMWEST (Phoenix) - Hold off on expanding the Terminal 4 parking
garage at Sky Harbor. Look at reshuffling the airline lineup at Sky
Harbor's three terminals. Bring in airline execs and sell them on
Phoenix. Mayor Skip Rimsza is sounding the charge, convinced that
America West Airlines will be sold and leave town. The mayor
announced Wednesday he is putting a 30-day hold on the parking
garage contract until the city can come up with a ``business plan''
on how to realign gates at an airport without America West's
dominant presence. Rimsza says his staff has concluded the merger
is all but inevitable. Meanwhile, airline analysts aren't as
certain that a sale will occur. By MARY JO PITZL. Story will move
in the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
