<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE CRITICS HAVE SPOKEN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   The closing argument of White House counsel  &UR; Charles Ruff &LR; ,
presented on Monday in the Senate trial of President Clinton,
received four stars from one of his toughest critics.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he has a sense of drama that's extraordinary,'' Ruff's
mother,  &UR; Margaret Carson &LR; , told the New York Times. `` &UR; Laurence
Olivier  &LR; couldn't do it any better.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Ian McKellen &LR; , nominated for a best actor Oscar this week for
``Gods and Monsters,'' was quoted in the Chicago Tribune as saying,
``What's very encouraging is to see  &UR; Edward Norton &LR; 's nomination
(for ``American History X''). He told me I was the reason he became
an actor. I hope I'm the reason he doesn't win an Oscar.''
</P>
<P>
   _ A first-class traveler on a recent flight from the East says
that he and his cabin-mates were having a wonderful time telling
jokes about the Clinton scandal, the sole exception being one
silent woman twitching in her attempt to appear stone-faced. By the
end of the flight, he realized she was Rep.  &UR; Anna Eshoo &LR; , D-Calif.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHAT TO DO AND WHAT NOT TO &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Among the cover stories in the useful teen magazine Twist:
``Fast Fixes for Sucky Sitches.'' One solution: ``Let yourself feel
sucky about what happened.''
</P>
<P>
   In the latest issue of Men's Fitness, on the other hand, is a
list of ``39 Things You Should Never Do,'' including:
</P>
<P>
   Don't say, ``I have no idea'' on the job; ``Never hold a glass
in your right hand at a cocktail party''; ``Never leave more than
two phone messages in a row.''
</P>
<P>
   Then there's conservatively dressed decorator  &UR; Ann Downey &LR; , who
told the New York Observer the secret of her unerring taste: ``I
don't decorate like I dress. I don't think best-dressed women
become the best decorators. ... A room needs more punch.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Marvin Jarrett &LR; , former publisher of Bikini and Ray Gun
magazines, is starting Nylon, a magazine for women in their 20s.
Creative director is supermodel  &UR; Helena Christensen &LR; , says New York
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Susan Margolis  &LR; found &UR; Cindy Crawford &LR; 's blurb for  &UR; Nancy &LR; 
 &UR; Etcoff &LR; 's ``Survival of the Prettiest: The Science of Beauty'' very
persuasive: ``Although I did not enjoy being called a `genetic
freak,' I did find Nancy Etcoff's book thought-provoking and a good
read _ yes, we can read, too.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Bob Backlund &LR; , a Connecticut Republican and former
professional wrestler, has announced his intention to run for
Congress in 2000, says the New York Daily News.
</P>
<P>
   _ McCall's magazine goes out on a limb with its ``What We Don't
Love'' list, which includes the surprising ``The whole family
having the flu at the same time.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Bradford University in England is offering an Internet-based
degree, says a report in the Telegraph of London, enabling students
to enroll, pay fees and study totally electronically.  &UR; Jerry
Matters &LR;  says he's looking forward to his bs.com degree.
</P>
<P>
   _ Residents of the Mission are holding a ``Luv-In'' at one of
the neighborhood's toughest corners, 16th and Mission, on
Valentine's Day, from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. Planners are hoping that
neighbors will gather to sing the praises of their 'hood. Also, if
you live in the Mission, &LR;  or grew up there and have old pictures,
family albums or stories to share, the Mission Branch of the Public
Library would like to see and hear them from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m.
March 7. Selected images and transcriptions of interviews will go
to the History Center Photo collection at the Main Library and to
the Mission branch library.
</P>
<P>
   _ Poets  &UR; Carolyn Kizer  &LR; and  &UR; Maxine Kumin &LR; , chancellors of the
Academy of American Poets, have resigned their positions in protest
of the lack of minorities on the board of chancellors, says Mode
magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Howard Stern &LR;  will have to appear in court in Brooklyn this
spring, reports the New York Post, to answer a suit by the family
of  &UR; Debbie Tay &LR; , who used to be known as ``The Space Lesbian'' on
his show and who overdosed four years ago. The suit claims that
``Stern's handling of the urn containing her ashes caused them
severe emotional distress.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I had a therapist in school. I thought it was extra credit to
take drug group and private therapy, so I took it.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Angelina Jolie describing her relationship with her family
and her father, Jon Voight, in Movieline magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
