<HEADER>
A9792 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPI &LR;      02-10 0443
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, Feb. 11, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet at 206-448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   OIL-SPILL (Coos Bay, Ore.) _ In a desperate move, Navy explosive
crews set off a series of charges below decks on the New Carissa,
hoping to start a massive fire that will burn off hundreds of
thousands of gallons of fuel. Officials said the move was their
last best hope. A powerful storm bearing down on Oregon would
likely rip the boat apart and the troublesome oil spill would
become an ecological disaster.
</P>
<P>
   By Rob Taylor and Scott Sunde. (Story will move in the ``a''
category.)
</P>
<P>
   OIL-SPILL-NAVY _ A look at the Navy Explosives Ordinance
Detachment from Whidbey Island NAS, Wash., which is blowing up the
fuel tanks on the freighter grounded off Coos Bay.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Offley. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   NAVY-LASER (Undated) _ Lt. Jack Daly, hit in the eye by a laser
allegedly fired from a Russian spy ship a year ago, will talk to a
congressional committee Thursday about his frustrations that the
military hasn't taken the incident seriously enough.
</P>
<P>
   By Ed Offley. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   HAHN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sometimes a kiss is just a kiss, sweeter
than wine but just something to build a dream on. Or something to
put in your pocket and take home like a souvenir ballpoint pen.
Scott Schaible, a 36-year-old eligible bachelor, has been
collecting kisses _ kiss impressions, anyhow _ for the last 16
years.
</P>
<P>
   By Jon Hahn. (Story has moved in the ``l'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-SEX (Undated) _ Sex is good. But I admit I feel uncomfortable
when every other joke on some sitcoms is a sex joke, or when every
other comedy ``situation'' involves a coupling, an attempted
coupling or a thwarted coupling. That doesn't make me a bluenose as
much as it makes me someone who sees a lot of bad TV. But I like it
even less when someone tries to mandate what TV ought to be doing.
It appears The Kaiser Family Foundation did that this week by
releasing a study of sexual content on TV.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Oakland) _ Seattle SuperSonics at the Golden State
Warriors.
</P>
