A9948 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-IMPEACHMENT-SHOUTER-T     02-10 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMPEACHMENT-SHOUTER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXASPERATED IMPEACHMENT SPECTATOR FREE, AWAITING HIS OWN TRIAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MARIA RECIO 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ A week after a spectator disrupted the Senate
impeachment trial by crying out, ``God almighty, take the vote and
get it over with,'' senators are preparing to do exactly that.
</P>
<P>
   And what of the man who voiced the sentiments of many Americans?
</P>
<P>
   Arrested, arraigned and now free awaiting trial, Richard Douglas
Llamas was released on his own recognizance a day after the Feb. 4
incident with orders not to come within a block of the Capitol.
</P>
<P>
   Llamas, 48, an unemployed carpenter, was charged with
``disruption of Congress,'' a misdemeanor. He faces up to six
months in jail and a maximum fine of $500 if found guilty. His
trial is set for April 19.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has a great interest in the Senate trial,'' said Llamas'
court-appointed attorney, Michael Madden. ``He does have a healthy
interest in politics.''
</P>
<P>
   The outburst, however, amounts to ``unlawful conduct inside the
Capitol,'' and must be prosecuted, said Channing Phillips,
spokesman for the U.S. attorney for the District of Columbia.
</P>
<P>
   Llamas generated a brief burst of publicity because of his
outburst. Madden said his client was treated as a celebrity in the
cell block where he was held for 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
   ``One of the marshals came back and shook his hand and said, `It
was an honorable thing that you did' and offered to buy him
dinner,'' the attorney said.
</P>
<P>
   Llamas has not wanted to comment since the incident. Madden said
the limited information he has about his client says that he is
from Northern California and served in the Navy during the Vietnam
War.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think he has an ax to grind with the government,'' the
attorney said.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
