<HEADLINE>
GRUDZIELANEK DECISION DUE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Perhaps the last piece of business in what was a
busy offseason for the Dodgers could come today.
</P>
<P>
   Shortstop Mark Grudzielanek, the lone Dodger involved in salary
arbitration, had his case heard Wednesday and a decision is
expected today.
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek asked for $2.6 million and the Dodgers countered
with a $1.9 million offer for the upcoming season. Eligible for
arbitration for the first time, Grudzielanek made $350,000 last
year.
</P>
<P>
   The 28-year-old is expected to battle with Jose Vizcaino for the
starting shortstop spot, unless general manager Kevin Malone can
pull the trigger on a trade before the season begins.
</P>
<P>
   Grudzielanek hit .264 with two homers, 21 RBI and six doubles
after being acquired by the Dodgers from Montreal in a July 31
trade.
</P>
<P>
   With both clubs, Grudzielanek hit .272 with 21 doubles, a
career-high 10 homers, 62 RBI and scored 62 runs. He also committed
33 errors but has spent much of the offseason working on his
fielding.
</P>
<P>
   Owners won the first two arbitration cases, defeating Boston
outfielder Midre Cummings and Expos infielder Shane Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   Uniform change: For the first time in 29 seasons the Dodgers
will brandish ``Los Angeles'' on their away jerseys, the club
announced.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers wore ``Los Angeles'' on their road jerseys from
1958-70 before moving to the familiar ``Dodgers'' scripted across
the chest.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, each player and coach will wear a ``Dodger Heroes''
patch on their uniform sleeve as a way to pay homage to past
Dodgers greats.
</P>
<P>
   First baseman Eric Karros selected a patch celebrating the
16-year career of former Brooklyn and Los Angeles first baseman Gil
Hodges.
</P>
<P>
   ``My dad rooted for the Brooklyn Dodgers and he was a big Gil
Hodges fan,'' Karros said. ``It was a really easy decision.''
</P>
<P>
   Each player will choose a former Dodgers hero from a list
developed through fan balloting on the Dodgers' Web site last
month. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
